  "response_text": "# Recovery-Focused Weekly Plan\n\n## Nutrition Principles\n- **Eat regularly** (3 meals + 1-2 snacks) to stabilize blood sugar\n- **Prioritize protein & complex carbs** for sustained energy\n- **Stay hydrated** (often fatigue signals dehydration)\n- **Limit caffeine** after 2pm to protect sleep\n- **Minimize processed foods** that cause energy crashes\n\n## Sample Weekly Menu\n\n**Breakfast options:**\n- Oatmeal with berries, nuts, yogurt\n- Scrambled eggs with whole grain toast\n- Smoothie: banana, spinach, protein powder, almond milk\n\n**Lunch options:**\n- Grilled chicken with sweet potato and vegetables\n- Lentil soup with whole grain bread\n- Salmon with quinoa and roasted broccoli\n\n**Dinner options:**\n- Turkey meatballs with whole wheat pasta\n- Baked white fish with brown rice\n- Bean chili with side salad\n\n**Snacks:**\n- Greek yogurt, nuts, fruit, hummus with vegetables\n\n---\n\n## Workout Routine (Gentle Recovery Focus)\n\n**Goals:** Build energy without depleting reserves; improve sleep quality\n\n### Monday\n- 20-min walk (outdoors if possible—sunlight helps)\n- 5-min stretching\n\n### Tuesday\n- 15-min gentle yoga or tai chi\n- 10-min breathing exercises\n\n### Wednesday\n- Rest day or 15-min leisurely walk\n\n### Thursday\n- 20-min walk + 10-min light strength (bodyweight only)\n- Focus: 2 sets of 8-10 reps\n\n### Friday\n- 15-min yoga or stretching\n\n### Saturday\n- 25-30 min moderate activity (walk, swimming, cycling—whatever feels good)\n\n### Sunday\n- Complete rest or 10-min gentle stretching\n\n---\n\n## Additional Recovery Practices\n\n- **Sleep:** Aim for 8-9 hours; maintain consistent bedtime\n- **Stress management:** 10 minutes daily meditation or journaling\n- **Social connection:** One meaningful interaction daily\n- **Breaks:** 5-minute breaks every hour if working\n- **Sunlight:** 15-20 minutes morning exposure\n\n**Important:** This is a starting point. If exhaustion persists, consult a doctor—it may indicate underlying conditions.",
